50|$|Heising {{played a}} major role in the {{development}} of military radio telephone systems in World War I, and for transoceanic and ship-to-shore public communications. He also conducted research on ultra-short waves, electronics, and piezoelectric devices, and invented important modulation systems including the constant potential system, the grid modulation system, the rectifier modulation system used in carrier telephony, and the constant-current or <b>Heising</b> <b>modulation</b> system, which was standard on most early radio telephone transceivers.|$|E

